cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the analysis of text data from Community Question and Answer (CQA) websites, which involves natural language processing and semantic analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to identify potential commercial campaigns, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also deals with detecting spam, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves analyzing user behavior and track records, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
